title: Assertion failed: `import.imported_module.get().is_none()`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: A-macros
labels.description: Area: All kinds of macros (custom derive, macro_rules!, proc macros, ..)

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
### Code Exact code unknown code. The error was generated by using `cargo check`. Rerunning after `cargo clean` did not fix this. Did not resolve this yet at the time of writing this. This might be related to: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/83336 But I think this was because I compiles first and got this error: ``` error: internal compiler error: expansion entered force mode without producing any errors --> controllers/src/server/launch_errors.rs:6:13 | 6 | error!("{}", err); | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ | = note: delayed at compiler/rustc_expand/src/expand.rs:460:34 ``` This was expected to give an error (needed to be `log::error!(...)` )
Full backtrace on the fist check:
